4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp program designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, along with practical skills to secure these environments.

Participants will learn about cloud security, penetration testing (offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The program also covers managing risks using data loss prevention (DLP) strategies and complying with international standards like ISO 27001 and NIST.

The Cybersecurity Bootcamp is a 16-week program that includes three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate, recognized by multiple institutions.

No previous experience is required to enroll in the program. Cybersecurity professionals in the United States earn a median annual salary of $103,560, making it a lucrative field to pursue.

For more information, visit the 4Geeks Academy website at: https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity

